description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Nurse or Allied Health Professional to join our team as a Band 5 Assistant Resuscitation Officer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with the Specialist Resuscitation Officer you will be developed and supported in helping the team provide basic and immediate life support training to identified staff, support and advise on physical health issues and provide associated training including First Aid and venepuncture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also assist with auditing of cardiac arrest procedures; including equipment within clinical areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to have excellent communication skills, have good presentation and teaching skills, use initiative and prioritise your workload effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The use of a vehicle to undertake any necessary travel in connection with the duties of the post is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this exciting opportunity and would like more information regarding this role please contact Debbie Burton Specialist Resuscitation Officer on 07392 314910 or email deborah.burton@swyt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
